text: Hey Gura, I wanted to give you something that I learned from watching Brew. He has a video that talks about a man that had really bad motion sickness that he discovered when he decided to live on a boat. It was so bad that he could not stay on a boat for very long. One day his son introduced him to VR and he discovered that it also gave him motion sickness. It gave him the idea to test it on a boat surprisingly enough it helped him get over motion sickness. The idea is create some kind of motion while you are playing VR that is similar to being out on the water or a vibration of some sort to make your body think it is moving when you are playing VR. It's not guaranteed to work on everyone, but it has a high percentage of working on people who got over motion sickness when they had to live on the sea.
